review_blob: From Can (from drankencentrale Rotsaert, Zedelgem for 9,95 euro) as it should be, but poured in a perfect glass (not like it should be). But I wanted to share ... My wife wanted to share. Nice golden colour with perfect stable and lacing head. Smell ... hmmm like perfect hops, just like the taste. Very soft and maybe the most balanced beer Ive ever tried. On this moment the nummer 3 IPA in the word and I understand why. Nice experience and worth the money!
Bottle from shop in kent. Dark black color, stable beige head. Oaky, roasted malts. Nice and complex one!

From bottle, shared with friends. Unstable small white head, dark brown color. Smell: very sweet, dried fruits, banana
 Just like the taste, alcohol... by far too sweet for me. Strange Yeasty aftertaste.
From 75 bottle, yellow colored with nice foamy white head! Smell: malty notes, yeasty. Taste, sec... hmmm average. But nice try.
From tap in irish pub. Very small and stable white head. Delicious malty nose, just like taste. Nice and very simple but so good.
In dubliners bar in gotheborg. From tap. White and stable lacing headn smell; spiced hops with malty notes. Taste, very balanced with nice hops, citrus notes, malty in the aftertaste. Nice one!
500c Bottle, nice fishermen bar, golden color with small white unstable head. Medium Malty smell, just like taste. Hoppy notes. Refreshing easy drinking beer. Decent.
Bottle, Foamy, amber colored beer with lacing small white head. Nice hops in the smell, spices. Taste well balanced, simple but very nice. Nice breadtaste in the aftertaste.
From shop near swedish border, dark yellow color, small and unstable head. Yeasty smell, a little boring taste. Nice try, but ive had much better beers in my life. But its my first swedish beer ever!
Yellow color, no head. Taste: very refreshing after a nice walk in nature. But I think thats a little subjective. Is very watery with a very small hoppy flavor. Not bad for the low alcohol.

bottle 75 cl, very licht yellow coloured with unstable white head. Typical lupulus smell (spiced), taste a little less taste then I expected, overall quit refreshing but not overwhelming. Easy drinkable beer but not at all the best beer from this brewer!
bottle, from friend on holiday in Austria, yellow golden colour with decent white head. Smell: some hoppy notes, a little sharp in the taste. Easy drinking beer.
from tap in Granada, light golden colour with unstable white head. Smell: some sweetness. Taste: watery, sweet notes. Typical beer to drink on hot summer days, very chilled.

In Malaga I asked for a beer and they gave me this. Bottle, yellow colour with very unstable white head. Alcoholic smell, just like the taste. I dont understand why they brew this... Very sweet and alcoholic taste, no palate. I like the lower alcohol one much more.

from bottle in oldest bar (400 years old) from Crdoba, Spain. Unless the bartender didnt know a thing about beers it was a nice place to drink that beer. Light Golden/yellow colour with foamy and lacing white head. Smell: some grassy and fruity notes, some maltyness and citrus. Taste: nice medium bitter, grassy, some fruityness, hoppy and herbal. I liked it to drink that one between al the ice beers in Spain. But Im sure Ive had much better Saisons in my life.

from tap, Andalucia 2014. Light golden colour with unstable white head. Smell: some sweetness, maltyness. Taste: very watery, some sweet and malty notes. Not a top beer at all, but nice to drink on hot summer days in Spain. It was my favorite one on my holiday. But it is still a very simple and monotone beer.
33cl can, super cold on a hot summer-day. Unstable white head, very watery smell. Taste: nothing special, very watery and some alcohol, light grassy and metal notes. Not good...

from tap in Granada, light golden colour with very unstable almoste unexisting head, smell .. some sweet malty notes. Taste: watery, refreshing on hot days. Not bad to drink over there, but as expected not a topper.

bottle 2009, dark brown colour with perfect beige head. Smell: roasted malts, coffee, chilli pepper. Taste: roasted malts, coffee, nice bitter stuff in the aftertaste. A little bit too overwhelming, over the top beer, but anyhow a very nice one.
beer_name: Struise Black Damnation IV - Coffee Club

review_blob: 1l can bought in Bonn, germany. Very small and unstable head, some grassy notes in the smell. Taste: ok, refreshing and grassy.

@ beaver street brewery in a glass, nice black coloured stout with foamy white and lacing head. Smell: roasted malts, some coffee, drops. Taste: nice balance between roasted malts and the bitterness. Very nice stout! But I dont understand the naming of sweet stout because it isnt sweet at all. Congrats!
beer_name: Beaver Street R & R Oatmeal Stout

review_blob: from tap @ brewery. Blonde coloured with small white head. So far so good. Malty smell with some fruity and sweet notes. Taste: no body, too sweet, some nice malty and fruity notes. Not my type of beer. A bit like the blonde leffe but ever worse. I didnt taste any bitterness in that beer. Sorry but not my style.
from tap @ brewing company. Small and not stable head. Smell: sweet, very sweet for a pilsener. Almost the worst beer ever from tap.
bought in shop near Flagstaff, from bottle in glass. Nice foamy white, lacing and stable head. Smell, citrus and very nice hops. Taste: hoppy, citrus. Nice and refreshing beer! Lovely one!
poured in a glass @ the beaver street brewery. Nice blond colour with some shining orange colour. Smell: hoppy, citrus, just like the taste Very refreshing beer with nice body. its a balanced IPA!

bottled, poured in a glass. Bought in LA and I think its a popular Belgian style beer in California. Brown-reddish colour with nice foamy head. Smell: fruity, malty and some sweetness. Taste: Plums, dried fruits and far too sweet. A little boring beer with some malty notes. Not my cup of tea. Reminds me a bit on the bruine leffe.
From supermarket in San Francisco. blond colour with nice lacing head. Smell: citrus, nice and fresh, taste: very nice bitterness, dry aftertaste. Nice first try-out of an American beer!
bottle from drankencentrale rotsaert, amber coloured with small white head. Smell: some sour, cherry. Taste: Yeasty notes, caramel, sour, cherry and other fruity notes. Very nice one!
beer_name: De Dochter van de Korenaar LEnfant Terrible

review_blob: bottle from dranken Geers, dark reddish coloured with very small white head. Cherry, woody smell. Taste: maybe some great fruity cherry .. Ooh, I didnt expect such a good one! Why are they retired?

bottle,from drankencentrale rotsaert. First time drunk it on the babs beerfestival. When I drink this one I was so proud that it was brewed to close to my house. Yellow/organge coloured with unstable white head, yeasty smell, apricot in the first taste that goes further to a nice fruity taste. Nice hops. In some way easy drinking, in some way heavently nectar. Thank you!

Bottle, from drankencentrale rotsaert.. Poored with very small head. Some lacing but overal very poor looks. Smell like a pils should be, taste: very average but not bad at all. I like the idea that a goot brewery like dupont makes some pils. Its decent, I wouldnt say no to that beer on a hot summer day. But its nothing compared with the saison dupont!

bottle from drankencentrale rotsaert. Nice to drink a new st bernardus beer. Yellow coloured with great foamy white head, lacing. Smell: koriander and other typical witbierstuff. Just like the taste: almonds, refreshing, koriander, ... One of the better witbierstyled beers!
bottle, golden colour with small although lacing head. Smell: fruity, apricot .. nice so far. Taste; very sweet, apricot, alcohol. Nice for a beer from france, but a bit too much sugar within.
bottle from Rotsaert, yellow coloured with foamy and lacing head. Smell: nice hops, fruity. Taste: very nice hopped, bitter, pear, nice flavour!
beer_name: De Dochter van de Korenaar Belle-Fleur IPA

review_blob: bottle from dranken Geers, very dark coloured with small beige head. Smell: coffee, tequilla. Taste: coffee, tequilla, very hoppy notes. Heavy one but Ive never tried something like this! Nice one but not to drink every month.
beer_name: Mikkeller Beer Hop Breakfast Aged In Tequila Barrels

review_blob: bottle, blond/amber coloured, yeast smell. Taste: yeasty, some very nice hops .. Nice one but I prever the normal hof ten dormaal.
beer_name: Stillwater / Hof Ten Dormaal Bronze Age

review_blob: bottle, dark amber/brown beer with foamy white head. Smell: some roasted malts, industrial, strange .. , Taste: roasted malts, some yeasts, grainy. Easy one, not bad, but also nothing special.
bottle, orange coloured with foamy white head. Smell: yeasty. Just like the taste: very yeasty, some fruity notes. Boring one with strange aftertaste.

33cl Bottle, from Dranken Geers, dark brown coloured with foamy, stable and lacing dark head.  Smell: industrial, some metalic. Taste: roasted malts, raisins, some malty and sweet notes. Not bad and simple palate, not blowing away.

bottle, yellow coloured with foamy, lacing and stable white head. Smell: yeasty, hoppy and fruity. Taste: nice and refreshing hops, some bitter notes and fruity in the aftertaste. Pefect easy drinking beer;

75cl bottle, shared with friends (2x), dark brown with foamy, lacing and stable white head. Smell: some hoppy notes, caramel, dark fruits. Taste: just great: a perfect balance between the fruity of a dark ale and the powerfull hoppyness of a IPA: caramel, chocolat, yeasty, hoppy. To try on a hot summerday! It was my list bottle, but Ill buy more of them!

75cl bottle shared with friends, dark brown coloured with foamy white/beige head. Smell: fruity notes, roasted malts, raisins, dark fruits. Taste: nice roasted malts, raisins, yeasty notes, some nice hops, coffee, chocolate, caramel. Reminds me on an imperial stout, nice brew!

33cl bottle from drankencentrale rotsaert, yellow colour with foamy, stable and lacing white head. Smell: some yeasty notes. Taste: yeasty, citrus, some hoppy notes. Nothing special but also nothing wrong with it, just a simple blond beer like you find many of them. Easy drinking.

bottle, golden colour with foamy, stable and lacing white head. Smell: some fruity notes, yeasty. Taste: the alcohol is very well hidden (I expected some 6,5 abv, but 8,5, I couldnt believe!), fruity notes, yeasty notes. Decent, but not that special. the Valeir Extra is more my style.

33cl bottle, dark blond/amber coloured with foamy and lacing white head, smell: very yeasty, sugary. taste: very yeasty, mild sweetness, some malty notes and fruity: pineapple.. butterscotch in the aftertaste. Nice one if you like yeasty beers cause its the headnote. Not a topper, but very decent.

bottle, vintage 2007, dark brown coloured with almost nog head. Some wine look a like. Smell: very rich: dark fruits, plums, chocolat, vanilla, some yeasty Taste: dark fruits, plums, chocolat, vanilla,very sweet sugar, some yeasty aftertaste. I like this one a lot! But you cant drink this
beer_name: Struise Pannept - Old Monks Ale - Pannepeut

review_blob: from a can (1+1 for free), carrefour. yellow coloured with white and stable head. Smell: some metallic, yeasty. taste: metallic, yeasty .. some strange industrial beer. Not my type of beer.

bottle, yellow coloured with small white head. Smell: some grainy-grassy smell. Taste: yeasty notes, grainy .. typical like the normal carlsberg, but some more alcohol within. Dont know why they made this one, but its ok untill the aftertaste who is some industrial.

bottle from carrefour, blond coloured with foamy white head. Some lacing stuff.. Smell: yeasty. Taste: some grainy, industrial notes, yeasty and toothpaste in the aftertaste. Im curious who likes this one.

Bottle from dranken Geers, Oostakker. Dark/Amber coloured with foamy and lacing white head. Smell: hops, some fruity notes, fresh; Taste: very bitter/hoppy, very refreshing, some peach. Well hidden alcohol. Herbal, drop, cereal. Very nice one! Id hope to have more of this stuff!
